<subSubSection id="C32F6564FFC8FF84FF2CFD09815473B9" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B8A36EFFFC8FF84FF2CFD0980FB758D" blockId="9.[151,713,729,756]" box="[151,713,729,756]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">
<heading id="D0C28183FFC8FF84FF2CFD0980FB758D" bold="true" box="[151,713,729,756]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FF2CFD0980FB758D" bold="true" box="[151,713,729,756]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FF2CFD098322758A" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,272,729,756]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FF2CFD098322758A" bold="true" box="[151,272,729,756]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Monardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FE21FD0980FB758D" authority="Kieffer, 1913" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1913" box="[410,713,729,756]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FE21FD098013758A" bold="true" box="[410,545,729,756]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Xylopriona</emphasis>
Kieffer, 1913
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36EFFFC8FF84FF2CFCF1815473B9" blockId="9.[151,1437,801,1439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FF2CFCF183277445" box="[151,277,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FF2CFCF183277445" box="[151,277,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Xylopriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as used here, is a quite heterogenous group gathering 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FC3DFCF181C77445" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1895" box="[902,1013,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FC3DFCF181C77445" box="[902,1013,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Monardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FB8AFCF186857445" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Hippa" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[1073,1207,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Micromyini">Micromyini</taxonomicName>
with claw-long empodia and leaf-shaped translucent antennal sensilla (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B1EFFC8FF84FD4FFC95865A7421" author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[756,1128,837,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" pagination="1 - 333" refId="ref13620" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2009) The Wood Midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae: Lestremiinae) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 18, 1 - 333." type="journal article" year="2009">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2009: 208</bibRefCitation>
). Defined in such a vague manner, this is no doubt an artificial grouping, maintained to avoid fragmentation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FBE4FCB986FC74FD" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1895" box="[1119,1230,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FBE4FCB986FC74FD" box="[1119,1230,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Monardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like micromyines into a plethora of monotypic or arbitrarily defined genera. The issue here is illustrated using the example of a new species, named 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FEFCFC6283C574B5" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[327,503,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FEFCFC62835474B5" box="[327,358,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FECEFC6283BC74B5" box="[373,398,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">X.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FE26FC6183C574B5" box="[413,503,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose male morphology perfectly fits 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FC0EFC61860174B5" box="[949,1075,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FC0EFC61860174B5" box="[949,1075,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Xylopriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except that the antennal sensilla are multi-branched (
<figureCitation id="130E2A6AFFC8FF84FEC7FC0583E27491" box="[380,464,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1807,1832]" captionTargetBox="[179,1406,464,1770]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[170,1416,453,1782]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Male morphology of Monardia (Xylopriona) abbreviata (15–16) and Monardia (Xyl.) obscura (17–18), holotypes. 15: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. 16: Genitalia, ventral. 17: Genitalia, ventral. 18: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scales 0.05 mm. Arrows refer to characters described in the diagnoses." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3707466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3707466/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). This 
<typeStatus id="548E884DFFC8FF84FDA5FC05807C7491" box="[542,590,981,1007]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">type</typeStatus>
of sensilla was previously unknown to occur in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FBC8FC0586CF7491" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Hippa" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[1139,1277,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Micromyini">Micromyini</taxonomicName>
. However, we refrain from assigning 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FE2CFC2A807B736D" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[407,585,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FE2CFC2A8384736D" box="[407,438,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FE7DFC2A83ED736D" box="[454,479,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">X.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FE54FC29807B736D" box="[495,585,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to a genus of its own because the merit of antennal sensilla morphology for the classification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FEC2FBCD83CD7349" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Hippa" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[377,511,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Micromyini">Micromyini</taxonomicName>
is a poorly understood issue. Adding to the problem, we know that the greater part of micromyine diversity is undescribed and to be found in the Eastern Palearctic, Oriental and Neotropical regions rather than in Europe (unpublished data). In other words, we have to accept that a sound generic revision of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FAF5FBB582EA73DD" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Hippa" baseAuthorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Micromyini">Micromyini</taxonomicName>
is not achievable on the basis of European material alone. The limiting factor for tackling a revision of world 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FF2CFB7D832F73B9" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Hippa" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[151,285,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Micromyini">Micromyini</taxonomicName>
is the lack of resources for such a laborious project.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32F6564FFC8FF84FF7CFB01870372E1" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8A36EFFFC8FF84FF7CFB01870372E1" blockId="9.[151,1437,801,1439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">
The other new 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FECBFB0183DC7395" box="[368,494,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FECBFB0183DC7395" box="[368,494,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Xylopriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described here is a member of the species group around 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FBD0FB0287AA7392" authority="(Felt)" baseAuthorityName="Felt" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1131,1432,1233,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toxicodendri" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FBD0FB0286B07395" box="[1131,1154,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">M</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FB21FB0286817395" box="[1178,1203,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">X.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FB79FB0187627395" box="[1218,1360,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">toxicodendri</emphasis>
(Felt)
</taxonomicName>
, a well circumscribed, monophyletic subset of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FD20FB25812B7271" box="[667,793,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FD20FB25812B7271" box="[667,793,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Xylopriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B1EFFC8FF84FCEEFB258688726E" author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[853,1210,1269,1296]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" pagination="1 - 333" refId="ref13620" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2009) The Wood Midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae: Lestremiinae) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 18, 1 - 333." type="journal article" year="2009">
Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2009: 
<specimenCount id="9D33FD66FFC8FF84FB30FB258688726E" box="[1163,1210,1269,1296]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" type="generic">212</specimenCount>
</bibRefCitation>
f.). The 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FAB4FB2587AF7271" baseAuthorityName="Felt" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1295,1437,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toxicodendri">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FAB4FB2587AF7271" box="[1295,1437,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">toxicodendri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group poses a twofold taxonomic problem, insofar as its relationship to other 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FC44FAC9864F724D" box="[1023,1149,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FC44FAC9864F724D" box="[1023,1149,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Xylopriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is obscure and the namegiving species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FEFDFAEE801E7229" baseAuthorityName="Felt" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[326,556,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toxicodendri" subGenus="Xylopriona">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FEFDFAEE836F7229" box="[326,349,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">M</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FECEFAEE83BC7229" box="[373,398,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">X.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FE25FAED801E7229" box="[414,556,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">toxicodendri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is now known to be a complex of several discrete species, not a morphologically plastic, cosmopolitan species as previously believed (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B1EFFC8FF84FC95FAB186A47205" author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[814,1174,1377,1403]" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" pagination="1 - 333" refId="ref13620" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2009) The Wood Midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae: Lestremiinae) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 18, 1 - 333." type="journal article" year="2009">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2009: 213</bibRefCitation>
). Unpublished material at our disposal suggests that there are at least eight different 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D6CFFC8FF84FC87FA5581F872E1" baseAuthorityName="Felt" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[828,970,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toxicodendri">
<emphasis id="B941EAFDFFC8FF84FC87FA5581F872E1" box="[828,970,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">toxicodendri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like species present in 
<collectingCountry id="F322767FFFC8FF84FB6BFA55871E72E1" box="[1232,1324,1413,1439]" name="Sweden" pageId="9" pageNumber="358">Sweden</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
